{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2f6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–32"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"460l–32"},"text":"§ 460l–32.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For the purposes of this part:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2f7-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–32/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Reclamation lands” means real property administered by the Secretary, acting through the Commissioner of Reclamation, and includes all acquired and withdrawn lands and water areas under jurisdiction of the Bureau.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2f8-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–32/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Reclamation program” means any activity authorized under the Federal reclamation laws (the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1902-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1902","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/32/388"},"text":"32 Stat. 388","children":[],"tail":", chapter 1093; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s371"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 371","children":[],"tail":")),"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002301"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002301"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. There should probably be only a single closing parenthesis. See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" and Acts supplementary thereto and amendatory thereof)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2f9-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–32/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Reclamation project” means any water supply or water delivery project constructed or administered by the Bureau of Reclamation under the Federal reclamation laws (the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1902-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1902","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/32/388"},"text":"32 Stat. 388","children":[],"tail":", chapter 1093; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s371"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 371","children":[],"tail":"),"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002302"},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002302"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"2","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" and Acts supplementary thereto and amendatory thereof)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2fa-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–32/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2fb-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/575/tXXVIII/s2803"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–575, title XXVIII, § 2803","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4691"},"text":"106 Stat. 4691","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id77c2c2f